-- BrasilAgro, Brasil Ecodiesel, Ecopetrol: Latin America Equity Preview
-- Alexander Ragir
-- 2010-06-25T04:09:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/brasilagro-brasil-ecodiesel-ecopetrol-latin-america-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Latin American trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous
close.  
 The  MSCI Latin America Index  dropped 1.7 percent to
3,817.80. In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-
traded class of stock.  
 Brazil  
 Cia. Brasileira de Propriedades Agricolas SA  (AGRO3 BZ):
BrasilAgro said Credit Suisse Hedging-Griffo Corretora de
Valores SA reduced its ownership of the company’s common shares
by almost 8 percent to 14.6 percent. The stock rose 0.6 percent
to 9.15 reais.  
 Brasil Ecodiesel Industria e Comercio de Biocombustiveis e
Oleos Vegetais SA  (ECOD3 BS): The biodiesel company said a court
dismissed the company’s appeal to reverse a year-long suspension
preventing its Itaqui and Iraquara units from selling biodiesel
in sanctioned auctions. The stock rose 4.5 percent to 93
centavos.  
 Log-in Logistica Intermodal SA  {LOGN3 BZ): The freight
transportation company named  Vital Jorge Lopes  chief executive
officer, replacing  Mauro Oliveira Dias , who is leaving next
month for personal reasons. The stock fell 2.1 percent to 6.46
reais.  
 Colombia  
 Ecopetrol SA  (ECOPETL CB): Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp.,
the operator of Colombia’s largest oil field, plans to invest as
much as $2 billion in 2011 and 2012 as it boosts production, the
company’s president said. Ecopetrol, Colombia’s state-run oil
company, rose 0.4 percent to 2,770.  
